<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-02-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-02-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="2" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.C114/445bbb</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-02-19">February 19, 1929</date>.</dateline>
                            <seg rendition="#left">No. 404</seg></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I am enclosing, for transmission in the
                            usual informal manner, a note to the Secretary-General of the League of
                                Nations,<note n="9" xml:id="d2fn9">Not printed.</note> setting <pb facs="0140" n="4" xml:id="pg_4"/> forth the text of a communication
                            which I have addressed to each of the signatories to the Protocol of
                            Signature of the Statute of the Permanent Court of International
                            Justice.</p>
                        <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Frank B. Kellogg</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>